            . My handkerchief was in my pocket - I did not feel it taken, but on hearing a scuffle I saw it in the prisoner's hand.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. The handkerchief was taken out of the pocket, and thrown at my feet - I took it up, and was going to give it to the gentleman; I told him who the lad was.</p>
